East Coast Radio reported that the 37-year-old woman from the Embo township is due to apply for bail. She was arrested last week and charged with child abandonment a crime that carries a penalty of up to 10 years imprisonment.The baby was reportedly discovered in the taxi by a nurse using it to get home from work.A note attached to the infant s top read: I apologise for what I did please forgive me. There is nothing I can do. The father is denying the baby. I don't have an ID to apply for a grant because I left it at home in the rural area. Please take good care of the baby or send it to the police. TMG Digital